Description: Automatic meeting recorder for Linux desktops
 Smart Meeting Recorder runs quietly in the background and notices when you join
 an online meeting or voice call - Zoom, Google Meet, Microsoft Teams, Discord,
 Slack, Webex or a browser call - by watching which application is using your
 microphone.
 .
 Instead of recording automatically it asks first: "Meeting detected. Start
 recording?". One click records your screen, microphone and (optionally) system
 audio; recording stops by itself when the call ends and the file is saved as
 <App>_<timestamp>.mkv.
 .
 A tray icon gives a live timer plus pause, resume and stop. Pausing excludes the
 paused time from the saved file. Your microphone and the caller are each
 loudness-normalised so both voices come out at a comparable level, and
 background noise is filtered from the mic.
 .
 Note: this release captures the screen via X11 (x11grab) and does not yet
 support Wayland sessions.
